**[1845, 02-04] Ms.A.1.2.15.13**

RDW to MWC; Dublin. Agrees with MWC, EQ, and WLG re: the Herald affair.
Recommends that Chapman read a biography of Thomas Arnold, headmaster of
Rugby School, whom he respects highly after reading his Life. “Truly
amongst all nations, kindred, tongues, & people, all creeds, all sects,
all shadings, there are honorable & worthy people.”


